SIMPLE: dabble
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dabble
<hw>Dab"ble</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧b"b'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Dabbled</conjf>
<pr>(d⟦acr⟧b"b'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Dabbling</conjf> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧b"bl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[Freq. of <ets>dab</ets>: cf. OD. <ets>dabbelen</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To wet by little dips or strokes; to spatter; to sprinkle; to
moisten; to wet.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Bright hair <xex>dabbled</xex> in
blood.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dabble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dabble
<hw>Dab"ble</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To play in water, as
with the hands; to paddle or splash in mud or water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where the duck <qex>dabbles</qex> 'mid the rustling sedge.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To work in slight or superficial manner; to do in a
small way; to tamper; to meddle.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Dabbling</xex> here
and there with the text.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Atterbury.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>During the first year at Dumfries, Burns for the first time began
to <qex>dabble</qex> in politics.</q> <rj><qau>J. C.
Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dabbler</ent>⟦br⟧
